{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c6ae9deb-45c2-4487-9a23-ec59d152bd7a","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest adapter entirely.** It now exclusively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the test runner. Since `vstest.console` relies on the VSTest adapter to discover tests, it finds nothing.\n\n**Fix:** Replace `vstest.console` in your CI with `dotnet test`:\n\n```bash\n# Before (broken with 4.x)\nvstest.console MyTests.dll\n\n# After\ndotnet test MyProject.csproj\n```\n\n`dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform in .NET SDK 8+, so it will discover and run your tests without any project file changes. Your `TestProject.csproj` and test code need no modifications — only the CI runner invocation needs to change.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f9761bd1-baf2-4cbf-ac4e-d297c7a73bc9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a known breaking change in MSTest.Sdk. Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.x, the default test runner was changed from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. In MSTest.Sdk 4.x, VSTest support was fully removed or disabled by default.\n\nLet me recall the specifics:\n\n- MSTest.Sdk/3.3+ introduced Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the default runner\n- In MSTest.Sdk/3.x, you could set `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` to use `dotnet test` with the new platform\n\n\n- Starting with MSTest.Sdk/3.4+, the VSTest adapter was no longer included by default\n- In MSTest 4.x, VSTest support was completely removed\n\nThe core issue is that MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest adapter entirely, so `vstest.console` can't discover or run tests anymore since it depends on that adapter. The fix is to migrate to `dotnet test`, which works with the Microsoft.Testing.Platform that's now the default.\n\nAlternatively, I can restore VSTest compatibility by enabling the bridge through the `<EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>` property in the project file, which lets the VSTest runner work with the new platform.\n\nActually, I need to clarify the version history here. MSTest.Sdk has evolved significantly—versions 3.3 and 3.4 introduced the Microsoft.Testing.Platform while maintaining VSTest support, but by 4.0 the VSTest adapter was removed entirely by default. The real solution is either migrating the CI pipeline to use `dotnet test` instead, which natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform, or explicitly re-enabling the VSTest bridge if staying with `vstest.console.exe`. The core issue is that `vstest.console` can't run tests from MSTest.Sdk 4.x projects since VSTest adapter support was removed entirely. The fix is to switch the CI pipeline to use `dotnet test` instead, which natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform, or downgrade to MSTest.Sdk 3.x if they need to keep using `vstest.console`.","outputTokens":1214,"requestId":"CFC8:16A6CA:E29B590:FCDAA12:69EC2C60"},"id":"561119a3-31b8-40af-a76e-63f452c80348","timestamp":"2026-04-25T02:52:40.974Z","parentId":"c91a8af5-8f21-4d45-a718-4f157d0dcb29"}
